            Burlington's extraordinary location between Lake Ontario and the Niagara Escarpment creates waterproofing challenges unlike anywhere else in the GTA. From lakefront properties in Aldershot dealing with fluctuating water tables to escarpment homes in Tyandaga managing limestone spring water, each elevation zone presents unique foundation protection requirements. With 186,000 residents and homes averaging 35-45 years old, Burlington's mature neighborhoods increasingly need specialized waterproofing expertise that accounts for the complex geology of glacial deposits transitioning from sandy lakeshore through clay mid-elevation to limestone bedrock.
